This repository is a fork of Monado (https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado).
The original Monado source files preserved here, identifiable by their
SPDX-License-Identifier headers, remain under their upstream licenses --
predominantly the Boost Software License 1.0 (BSL-1.0). The full text of every
license referenced by any file in this repository is available under LICENSES/.

New files authored by Marko Kazimirovic <kazimirovicmarko@photon.me>, as well
as substantive modifications to upstream files, are licensed under the GNU
General Public License version 3.0 or later (GPL-3.0-or-later). The full text
of GPL-3.0-or-later is available at LICENSES/GPL-3.0-or-later.txt.

Per-file rule of thumb:

  - A file's `SPDX-License-Identifier` header is the authoritative statement
    of that file's license.
  - Files entirely authored by Marko declare `GPL-3.0-or-later`.
  - Files originally from upstream Monado that have been substantively
    modified declare `GPL-3.0-or-later` as well; the original copyright lines
    (Collabora, Khronos, individual contributors, etc.) are preserved per
    BSL-1.0 terms, which permit relicensing.
  - Files originally from upstream Monado that have not been substantively
    modified retain their original SPDX identifier (typically BSL-1.0).
  - Vendored third-party code (under `samples/*/vendor/`, `src/external/`)
    retains its upstream license; do not assume GPL-3.0 applies there.

When the work is distributed as a whole (binary or source archive), the
combined work effectively follows GPL-3.0-or-later, because GPL is the more
restrictive of the two licenses and propagates to the linked product. The
BSL-1.0 portions remain individually distributable under their own terms when
extracted in isolation.

For a high-level summary of which subsystems were modified vs upstream Monado,
see MODIFICATIONS.md at the repository root.
